President Biden delivered a speech in the East Room of the White House during a Hanukkah celebration. He expressed gratitude to those in attendance and emphasized the importance of the Jewish community. Biden acknowledged the significance of Hanukkah as a story of miracles and resilience. He also addressed recent events, including the surge of anti-Semitism and the conflict in Israel. Biden reiterated his commitment to the safety and security of the Jewish people and Israel. He shared personal experiences of visiting Holocaust sites and emphasized the need to confront hate and silence. The President discussed his administration's efforts to combat anti-Semitism and promote equality and justice. He concluded by highlighting the resilience of the Jewish people and the importance of hope and faith.